<BLOCK1><TI>ORDER</TI>
<P><BOLD>THIS APPEAL</BOLD>, made by the Plaintiff, from the judgment of the Honourable Mr. Justice Myers pronounced on November 28, 2016, for an order that the said judgment be set aside and an order be made granting judgment for an increased verdict, or in the alternative that a new trial be ordered, together with costs, was heard today at Osgoode Hall, 130 Queen Street West, Toronto, Ontario.</P>
<P><BOLD>ON READING</BOLD> the notice of appeal, the material contained in the appeal books and compendiums of both parties, the factums of both parties, and on hearing the submissions of the appellant and of counsel for the respondents,</P>
<P>1. <BOLD>THIS COURT ORDERS</BOLD> that this appeal is dismissed.</P>
<P>2. <BOLD>THIS COURT ORDERS</BOLD> that the amount of the jury verdict is not increased and that there not be a new trial.</P>
<P>3. <BOLD>THIS COURT ORDERS</BOLD> that there be no costs of this appeal.</P>
